definition:
A man living at the time of Exile and Return, only mentioned at Neh.12.35; 
 son of: Jonathan (H3129K); 
 brother of: Shemaiah (H8098V), Azarel (H5832J), Milalai (H4450), Gilalai (H1562), Maai (H4597), Nethanel (H5417P), Judah (H3063K) and Hanani (H2607K)
 § Zechariah = "Jehovah remembers"
 11th in order of the minor prophets; a priest, son of Berechiah and grandson of Iddo, who, along with Haggai, directed the rebuilding of the temple in the days of Zerubbabel
